name: 17 min from City Center, 50 sqm, Free Parking
description:
Oktoberfest is close enough to get there in about ten minutes. But it is far enough to avoid myriads of drunk Oktoberfest people when you want to spend a quiet night. To get ready for a new day, enjoy a cosy environment that feels like home.
Why not having your morning coffee on a beautiful balcony or veranda overlooking garden and park?
neighborhood_overview:
Just a few steps from the house there is a butcher, a bakery, two cafés, and a comprehensive set of deli markets and drugstores, including a vast choice of fresh organic food. A few minutes walk away there is a bank, post office, car rental, fitness studios, doctors and restaurants – and last but not least: one of Munichs biggest and most traditional Beergardens, where you can experience true Bavarian lifestyle all year round, just two metro-stops away from Oktoberfest...
This apartment is in a quiet green neighbourhood, but very well connected to various public transports and to major freeways and Autobahns. Transportation to the very city center and to fabulous Schwabing night life is around 15 min by public transport around the clock.
You also can enjoy one of the most beautiful and traditional beergardens in Munich, 5 min on foot away. There are restaurants, deli shops, supermarkets, bakery, butcher from 50 meters to 200 meters away.
Don't miss Westpark with its fab
host_about:
I feel as a local and an international citizen at the same time. I love meeting people from all over the world, I love travelling. And I love to share my personal favorites in and around Munich. For all those who want to get in touch with Munich lifestyle, little escapes into nature, good food - don't hesitate to ask me!
Lean back and feel welcome!

name: Cozy appartment in Schwabing
description: The apartment is close to the park and not far from Leopoldstraße, cafes, restaurants & small shops  are right around the corner. Two minutes to the subway, bus & tram, which quickly lead to the city center in 5 minutes.
neighborhood_overview: I like the atmosphere here in this part of Munich. You only go out to the front door and see you right in life, with cafes, various international restaurants. The whole thing has a 'community' character. Various bakeries, kiosks and a very diverse Asia shop are around the corner. And don't forget, Schwabing is known for having a hairdresser on practically every corner in case you ever need one. Recently there are also spas, wellness & massage and of course the Nordbad with sauna...and it is only a few minutes to the fantastic Luitpoldpark...with joggers, bikers, walkers, football, or simply people who enjoy nature - and there is also a great beer garden with restaurant here. It's just minutes by train to Oktoberfest.
host_about: I am a passionate gardener & nature girl, enjoy winter camping at the seaside but warm weather as well. I fancy a good meal, love cooking and trying out recipes from other cultures. Reading a book is just as relaxing as well. I grow my  vegetables, fruits and herbs in my garden at home near Stuttgart, where I spend my weekends. I am a WE commuter to my little family with  2 kids and a lovely husband. My apartment  in Munich is centrally located, with nice parks in walking distance,  the park round the corner leads to the Olympic Park and its a nice walk to the English Garden as well. Although having a hunch for nature, I definitely need a clean apartment to feel 'home' and comfortable.

Ground floor, quiet inner yard, separate unit with separate entrance.
neighborhood_overview:
Today’s city district Haidhausen, which used to be located before the city gates of Munich, came to existence in the late 19th century and characterized by glorious historic buildings. Haidhausen has a history of craftsmanship that dates back even further - even some of the old hostelries are still preserved.

Our apartment is located in a three-minute-walking range of all important public transport connections, has a ground-level entrance and is surrounded by a quiet inner yard.

In the neighborhood you will find everything you need for a comfortable stay: shopping facilities, cafes, restaurants, a shopping mall, a cinema and tiny familiar shops.

The museum bus line will bring you to all museums in the inner-city. The Marienplatz, the Viktualienmarkt and the Church of Our Lady can also be reached in only a fifteen minute’s walk. We would also recommend a walk to the Englischer Garten (English Garden) along the river Isar.

name: Quiet & Green Oasis; 10Mins to City+close to River
description:
Hello there! As I travel a lot (mostly for sailing or hiking), my small flat in the middle of Munich is often vacant. During this time, I like to rent it out to other travellers. It's fully equipped and ready for your trip to Munich.

My flat is located in a quiet neighbourhood, close to the Isar river and it has good public transport connections that take you to the city centre in a few minutes. The appartment is a quiet oasis with lots of green plants.
neighborhood_overview: The neighbourhood is pretty quiet too. I hardly get to hear my neighbours and the street has very little traffic. It's a great place to enjoy the quiet part of Munich and also good to work in a quiet atmosphere. Several small supermarkets are just a few minutes walk away and there are a number of restaurants here in the area. I'd be happy to give you some local tips. The appartment is only a few blocks away from the Isar river, which invites you to great walks along the water and you can escape the hectic city life in the green part of Munich. Moreover, the zoo is around the corner and the "Flaucher", a hotspot for young people who meet for barbecues on mild summer nights, is within walking distance.

name: Beautiful Apartment close to Munich town center
description:
In the Herzogpark (Bogenhausen), one of Munich's most popular residential areas, close to the city and yet in the countryside, we offer this beautiful, completely newly renovated and furnished, very quiet apartment with furnished kitchen, bathroom and walk-in closet as well as a cozy garden seating area.

Modern 35 sqm appartment close to the Munich town centre in a very quiet and secure neighborhood with elegant villas but only 10min/car and 20min/bike to the city center. Public transport available.
neighborhood_overview:
The Herzogpark is a small residential area, directly on the Isar, opposite Schwabing on the English Garden. Beautiful walks lead into the city to the Hofgarten and in just 20 minutes by bike you can reach Marienplatz Square with a ride only through the greenery. Various beer gardens can be easily reached in 10 – 20 minutes, Schwabing in 10 minutes without parking problems and traffic congestion. You will find a supermarket, hairdresser, delicatessen, cosmetics, bank and pharmacy at Kufsteiner Platz, which can be reached in 2 minutes by car. Bakery and breakfast coffee in 1 min.
There are plenty of parking spaces. A car is not necessary for city visits.
Two bicycles can be rented daily or for the entire stay. Please make a reservation in advance.

The „Herzogpark“ is a small and exclusive living area, located at the river „Isar“ and the „English Garden“ a very beautiful park that is one of the largest city-parks in the world. Like in NYC it’s located in the middle

neighborhood_overview:
The house is situated in a quiet and secure residential area, 15min walk south of westpark. In the neighborhood there are plenty of restaurants, cafés and shops.
In 2 min walking distance from the house there is a bakery with terrace where you can also have breakfast. A fruit shop, a butchery (Bavarian sausage specialties) with lunch offers and a cheese shop are nearby.
For walking or sports activities the south park (8min walk) and the west park (15min walk) are perfect. The westpark is special because of its garden and lakescape, a beer garden and a restaurant. In summer (June 3rd - September 6th) there is also a popular open air cinema.
host_about:
Auch wenn ich gerne verreise, freue ich mich immer wieder auf München. Wohne schon seit 35 Jahren in dieser schönen Stadt an der Isar und kann Dir deshalb bestimmt wertvolle Tips für deine Ausflüge geben.
Die umliegende Natur mit den Seen begeistern mich jedesmal aufs Neue. Auf deinen Besuch freue ich mich.
Herzliche Grüße Irene

Even though I like to travel, I am always happy to come back to munich again. I have been living in this lovely city on the isar for 35 years now and I can for sure give you some tips for your stay here in munich. The surrounding nature and lakes inspire me every time again. I am looking forward to getting to know you.
Best wishes Irene

Just around the corner with us is a very tasty Bavarian restaurant, Franzz.

name: "Artist´s Creative Residence" 100m² im Zentrum
description: Here, the world of art is combined with high living comfort. Transient rooms, sliding and mirror walls make sleeping and enjoying in the 103m² studio to be an experience. The elegant minimalist ambience was created by the artist Georg Weiss and consists of large-format original works realized in-house and originals of the Bauhaus. An extendable  cinema screen of 12m², AppleTV, wireless IPhone and IPad connection allows home cinema dimension
neighborhood_overview: In the lively neighborhood you will find a lot of good Restaurants and nice bars.
host_about:
Auf unserern Reisen hat Georg Weiss und ich herzliche Gastfreundschaft erlebt. Ich möchte diese Freude an meine Gäste weitergeben, sie persönlich Willkommen heißen und mit Ihnen, sofern sie es wollen, näher in Kontakt kommen. In jedem Fall werde ich für sie ständig telefonisch zu erreichen sein.
Zu meiner Person:
Ich habe in Wien Angewandte Kunst, Design-Mode studiert. Ich war, und bin  Anhängerin von Modern Jazz und zeitgenössischer ernster Musik. Dadurch und durch einen Zufall habe ich den Künstler Georg Weiss kennen gelernt , der in Wien an der Akademie der Bildenden Künste studiert hatte. Aus der Faszination an seiner Person und zu seiner Welt wurde eine  mehr als 45 Jahre dauernde Lebensgemeinschaft in der ich auch seine  Assistentin war.  Ich freue mich, dass sich meine Gäste im Atelier, in dem gesamte Ambiente, über 100m², wohl fühlen. "Artist´s Creative Residence" ist ein großzügiger und angenehmer Ausgagngspunkt, München zu erkunden und zu genießen, und ein wohltuender Ort, um danach Ruhe und Erholung zu finden.
Was wichtig ist für mich:
Achtung... Zuwendung... Fairness... Ehrlichkeit... Zuverlässigkeit 
"Body andt Soul"
 Kultur Kunst Wissenschaft Freiheit 
 "Teilen macht reich"
" I had a dream...."

neighborhood_overview: Here we would like to refer to a description of the Munich homepage: Bogenhausen is one of Munich's top residential areas and is a district with many faces. Bogenhausen is one of the most diverse urban districts at the transition from a densely built city centre to the surrounding area. Gradually, the Gründerzeit buildings and noble villas give way to the post-war residential blocks and spacious green spaces. Bogenhausen may be a welcome alternative for those looking for more tranquillity than Isarvorstadt, Schwabing or Haidhausen can offer. At many corners of the borough, you don't notice that you're still in a city of millions. In addition to its outstanding sights, the old Bogenhausen is also worth a walk due to its numerous Art Nouveau villas: the district was designed as alarge, representative villa and rented house district according to uniform urbanplanning principles from the latefoundingdays. Mainly spared from severe wardamage, its original character has remained largely inta

name: Private Room Oktoberfest/ Theresienwiese
description:
Hello everyone, and welcome to my home. I live in a cozy flat just around the corner of the Oktoberfest venue (5 minutes by foot) and 5 minutes to city center - central station by underground - two stops.
The neighbourhood is well located nice, super safe, and clean, with a lot of restaurants and cafés.

The underground stop- “Schwanthalerhöhe” and public busses are in walking distance (3 minutes). Supermarkets, restaurants and cafés are just around the corner.
neighborhood_overview:
A grocery store is just around the corner. Some nice bars and restaurants and the Theresienwiese where the Oktoberfest takes place is really close (in walking distance about 5 minutes) and worth a visit. The famous Bavarian Augustiner Brewery is pretty close as well. Where you can get authentic Bavarian food and delicious beer.
Public transportation is in walking distance.
Underground U4/U5 - 3 minutes on foot. Underground station „Schwanthalerhöhe“
S-Bahn to the city center (Donnerbergerbrücke) and to the airport (15 Minutes on foot)
You can reach the Messe Munich by public transportation within 25 minutes.

name: Central Oktoberfest apartment, beautiful view
description: Our spacious and fully equipped 2 room apartment is located in a prime location in Schwabing! Relax on the spacious balcony or enjoy the surroundings in the Luitpoldpark. The Oktoberfest is only about 15 minutes away. The transport links by bus, streetcar and subway allow you to explore the city without any problems.  With a comfortable bed and a sofa bed, the apartment offers enough space for up to 4 people, if needed we can provide 2 additional mattresses.
neighborhood_overview:
Our apartment is located directly at the Luitpoldpark, the perfect place to escape from everyday life and enjoy the fresh air. Whether you want to jog, go for a walk or explore the numerous playgrounds with your children, the Luitpoldpark offers something for everyone. In winter, the park offers Munich's most popular and fastest sledding hill!

Just a 10-minute walk away is the well-known Olympiapark, which serves as a venue for numerous events and activities.

Culture and car enthusiasts will appreciate the nearby BMW Museum, which is also just 10 minutes away and offers a fascinating insight into the history and innovations of the automotive industry.

In the summer months, a picturesque beer garden just 5 minutes from our apartment invites you to socialize over cool drinks and hearty Bavarian specialties.

Experience Munich's charm and diversity in our beautiful and attractive apartment, which serves as the perfect base for all your adventure
host_about: Hi, we are Valentin and Iris. We are both living in this apartment if we are not on vacation :) We like to cook with our friends in our apartment. Furthermore, we are traveling a lot and that is the reason why we sometimes rent out our apartment. Hopefully you like our apartment the same as we do!

name: Springfest (Munich) Teepee All-Inclusive Camping
description: Springfest, often referred to as “little Oktoberfest”, is one of the world’s greatest beer festival and a bucket list must. Stoke Travel’s all-inclusive package includes festival entry, teepee accommodation (up to 8 people) with camping mattresses and sleeping bags, a cooked breakfast every morning and a delicious dinner every evening, our world-famous Stoketoberfest campsite parties, guides to direct you to the beer halls and an international crowd of like-minded travellers to party with.
host_about:
We’re the favourite choice for the backpacker on a budget, the student with some study-abroad holidays to burn, the gap year gapper looking to do something outrageous, the solo traveller searching for travel buddies, soul mates, or just somebody to have a (lot of) laughs with, or the group looking to travel with an even bigger group of absolute legends.
Our Stokies want the most affordable experiences at the world’s wildest, most popular and craziest festivals and destinations with an authentic feel, a flexible schedule and options to suit your budget. The best fiestas are easily accessible with our low cost, high fun trips. You could say travel parties and festivals around Europe are our jam.

name: Charming loft in the heart of Munich
description:
Lehel is a district of Munich with a majority of representative monument protected buildings. Also the apartment house (7 apartments) where the flat is located is monument protected.
The loft is spanning across two floors and it is located close to the Isar, the famous Maximilian-Street and the Prinzregenten-Street.
The location is very central, but nevertheless quite calm as the flat is located at a side street with very little traffic.
neighborhood_overview:
To the east there is the Maximilianeum, where the Bavarian Parliament resides.
In direction to the north at the Prinzregenten-Street there is the Haus der Kunst with the Golden Bar and the P1 club & bar. To the south at the Maximilian-Street I recommend the Brenner restaurant and of course close to the the luxury hotel Four Seasons and of course fashion and jewelry shops for the demanding clients.
Further to the west there is the Odeonsplatz and close to the south the Marienplatz.

name: CASA Mozart am Goetheplatz
description:
CASA Mozart - Central.Amazing.Studio.Apartment.

for 2 people at Goetheplatz, Munich Central Station (1.4 km), metro, bus and taxi 50 m away, 750 m walk to the city center, perfect location!

The 35 sqm studio apartment is located in a residential building in the DG and can be reached by stairs or elevator.

Facilities: a queen size bed, wardrobe, garage, kitchenette, dining table with chairs, living area with TV, couch, relaxing armchair with footstool and bathroom.
neighborhood_overview:
Surroundings

In the immediate vicinity of the studio apartment there are supermarkets, bakeries, cafes, bars, banks, drugstores, pharmacies and clinics.

The Theresienwiese, where the Oktberfest takes place, is in the immediate vicinity of our studio apartment (400m).

The trendy Glockenbach district with its bars, boutiques, art scene and cafés is a 10-minute walk away.

The center (Marienplatz) with the town hall and the famous "Glockenspiel" or the "Frauenkirche" are only two metro stations (5 minutes) away. You can even walk, it is only 1.7 km (20 min) from our studio apartment.

In the vicinity of Marienplatz there are many other tourist attractions such as the church „Alter Peter“, the "Residenz", the "English Garden", many well-known galleries, the "Hofbräuhaus" or the "Viktualienmarkt".

Our apartment is also suitable as a starting point for a walk along the Isar, as the river is only 1.5 km away.

Many
host_about: Wir sind sehr neugierig, aufgeschlossen und offen für Neues. Wir reisen viel, um andere Kulturen kennenzulernen. Wir lieben den Austausch mit anderen Menschen. Wir freuen uns auf jede neue Begegnung, denn sie inspiriert uns.

host_about:
Hi guys,

I'm a laid back but still responsible guy, very easy going who likes travelling a lot and getting in touch with people from all over the world.

I love doing sports, going out, doing barhopping, scuba diving and being active in every way. 
But I can also chill :) 
I speak German, English, Spanish, Italian and French.

I hope to find new friends from all over the world with AirBnB.
I'm looking forward to host you here in Munich or see you around somewhere in your favorite city.
Take care and see you soon,

host_about: I run a contemporary art gallery in Munich.  The Art Lofts above the gallery are rented out to visitors who enjoy art and/or our very special location in the midst of the Munich art scene.  I am 65 years old, speak German and English, live in Munich & Minnesota and love art and sports.

name: Brera "Cosy" Apartment - Your Short Stay Rate
description:
The philosophy of Brera Serviced Apartments is inspired by the vibrant Milan district of the same name "Brera". It stays for design, fun and creativity.

Our Brera Serviced Apartmenthouse has 58 Apartments over 6 Floors and an elevator. You will find your host and the housemanager in the office in the courtyard from Monday to Friday, from 8am-6pm, if you need any help they will be happy to help you.
neighborhood_overview:
Stay in our friendly apartmenthouse, located west of the city center. The central location is the perfect starting point for a carefree stay in the city. Couple of shops, bars and restaurants are around.

The public transport can be reached after a two minutes walk. You can easily reach the city center, airport or exhibition by public.
host_about:
Herzlich Willkommen bei Brera Serviced Apartments München! 
Ich freue mich, dich in der Weltstadt mit Herz begrüßen zu dürfen. Bei Fragen helfe ich dir gerne weiter und teile meine Insider Tipps mit dir! 
Das Apartmenthaus verfügt über 58 voll ausgestattete Apartments in verschiedenen Größen. Die Lage direkt an der U-Bahn Haltestelle Westendstraße ist der perfekte Ausgangspunkt für deinen Aufenthalt. 

Bei regelmäßigen Events kannst du deine Nachbarn und mich näher kennen lernen. Schau auf unserer Website vorbei, wann das nächste Event statt findet. 

CIAO und bis bald, 
dein Egor

neighborhood_overview:
Munico is located in the Obergiesing district, where there are many beautiful corners within walking distance. With its proximity to Untergiesing, which attracts more and more young and creative people with its many cafés and bars, it is located in a popular residential area.
Nearby is also the district Ramersdorf, with its many idyllic settlements and its historic town centre. Munich's oldest beer garden, the "Alte Wirt", is located here. With its church Maria, the district has one of the most important pilgrimage sites in Bavaria.
This district is also an important traffic junction in Munich and is therefore often called the "Gateway to the South". Thanks to the good connections, from here one is not only quickly in Munich's city centre and the trade fair city, but also close to beautiful local recreation areas such as the Ostpark or Perlacher Forst.

name: Single Apartment with kitchenette close to Isar
description: Living in a prime location and still quiet: our single flats with equipped kitchenette, own living, dining and sleeping area and home office space (free wifi) are located in the middle of the iconic Glockenbachviertel, directly on the beautiful Isarhochufer Ideal for jogging or walking, perfect for working, perfect for enjoying. And nice and smart for those who want to stay longer and feel a bit at home even when they're far away.
neighborhood_overview:
Here you can experience Munich as its best! The Bavarian capital is the city with the highest quality of life in Germany. And apartments on the Isar and in the Glockenbachviertel are among the most sought-after hot living spots within Munich. Because here you can not only jog and walk for miles. Here it is colorful, lively, vibrant and just really nice to work, live, jog, stroll or even walk your four-legged friend. Dogs are of course welcome here.
In the direct vicinity of the Apartment Hotel are the iconic Nockherberg, the Prater and the Weideninsel, the Westermühlbach and the so beautiful Rosengarten. Within walking distance and with direct access to any number of individual stores, stores, supermarkets, trendy pubs and bars, on our doorstep is the Röcklplatz, which offers a real culinary culture, the Evergreen Cafe Szuzi, the in restaurant Fugazi in Bauhaus style with Mediterranean cuisine and of course the Wittelsbach and Reichenbach Bridge with its legendary 24-hour Reichenb
host_about:
Wir bieten Dir ein zweites Zuhause im Glockenbachviertel inmitten von Szenekneipen, trendigen Cafés und direkt neben der Isar. Ideal zum Joggen oder Spazieren, wunderbar zum Arbeiten und Leben und vor allem großartig zum Genießen. Wir freuen uns Dich in unserem Living Hotel Prinzessin Elisabeth willkommen zu heißen.

We offer you a second home in the Glockenbachviertel in the middle of trendy pubs and cafes, right by the Isar. Ideal for outdoor activities, wonderful for working and everyday living our Living Hotel Prinzessin Elisabeth is aplace to enjoy. We're looking forward to welcoming you and becoming your second home in the most beautiful district of Munich.

description: Comfort made easy. New job, Unibeginn or city trip? And: we are very centrally located at the German Museum in Haidhausen, right on the Isar where Munich is colorful and lively and you can walk everywhere
neighborhood_overview: Here, in the Haidhausen district, many Munich people prefer to live, because here you get the best of two worlds: Munich pulsates here. It's colorful, creative and  cosmopolitan, but also green and completely relaxed. From the hotel, you can take public transport, which starts right outside the door, within minutes to the most beautiful and exciting corners of the city: Maximilianstraße, Marienplatz, Viktualienmarkt, Wiener Platz or the Museum Triangle in Schwabing. But here you are already in the middle of city life and can easily walk to the neighborhood from the Gasteig cultural center to the Isar, the Müllersche Volksbad, the Deutsche Museum, the Stadtcafe Film Museum, the shopping street Motorama and also the oldest cinema in the city "Die Museum Lichtspiele" on foot.
host_about:

name: Apartment in the Living Hotel at the Olympiapark
description: Quiet and smart living in our renovated one-room apartments at the Olympiapark. Whether short- or longstay, business or leisure, everything is taken care of here: Home meets office style including kitchenette, dining, working and living area, marble bathroom. A laundry is available in-house, as well as free high-speed wifi, green electricity and a smart hygiene concept. And: we are centrally located in Neuhausen, where Munich is colorful and you can easily get everywhere on foot.
neighborhood_overview: We are right in the middle of one of the most popular residential areas of the city: in Nymphenburg, Neuhausen and Gern free living space is hotly sought after, because here it is incredibly beautiful and very green: from the hotel you are in a few minutes walk directly in the Olympic area with its many sports, leisure and sightseeing opportunities such as Sea World, BMW Museum, the TV tower, the ice rink and the large weekend flea market. Just as quickly, you can walk to the Dante Stadium, which also has its winter outdoor swimming pool open during the cold season, or to the Taxispark and the associated Taxis beer garden: a real highlight, especially in the summer. For coffee and cake connoisseurs, we recommend the insider tip Café Tribeca at the end of the street. An extra plus point is the proximity to Nymphenburg Palace with its parks, the two driveways and the canal, the best place in town for curling or ice skating in winter.

All important stations of the city center are within walking distance.
Marienplatz, Karlsplatz-Stachus, Hauptbahnhof, Sendlinger Tor, Oktoberfest all a few minutes walk away
neighborhood_overview:
MUNICH FINEST APARTMENTS provides accommodation with city views and free WiFi ideally located in the center of Munich, within a short distance of Sendlinger Tor, Karlsplatz (Stachus) and Asamkirche.

Each unit features a kitchen with a dishwasher and a microwave, a safe, a flat-screen TV with satellite channels, ironing facilities, a wardrobe and a seating area. The private bathroom comes with a bidet, a hairdryer and free toiletries.

Popular points of interest near the apartment include Frauenkirche, Theresienwiese and Marienplatz. The nearest airport is Munich Airport, 29 km from MUNICH FINEST APARTMENTS.

According to independent guest reviews, this is the most popular part of Munich.

name: Locke Studio at Schwan Locke
description:
Welcome to your new mid-century-inspired base in the Bavarian capital, minutes from the site of Oktoberfest.

The vibe is one of calm creativity. The community is open and inclusive. And the apartments are both spacious and sophisticated. Settle in and see a side to Munich most tourists miss.
neighborhood_overview:
In Munich for Oktoberfest, Frühlingsfest or the Tollwood Winterfestival? You couldn’t stay in a better-located hotel or apartment. Just minutes from Theresienwiese, Schwan Locke offers an inspiring tranquil retreat in the midst of the action.

Our local borough, Isarvorstadt, includes the pretty neighbourhood of Glockenbackviertel, with its coffee shops, gay bars, global foodie spots and independent shops. And if your itinerary includes sightseeing time, we’re just a few tram stops from the city’s main attractions too. Including Marienplatz, the Viktualienmarkt, Beergarden Augustiner Keller and the museum quarter. Munich, done properly.

description: Where wellness meets hedonism. Urban grit meets leafy tranquillity. Your place to stay truly becomes your space to live. The first Locke of its kind.

Munich. City of history, tradition, innovation, art and music. And – unknown to many – a city of glorious open spaces and greenery, too. Stay at WunderLocke and you’ll be in prime position to explore it all.
Close to the city centre, the main sights are just 15 minutes away by tube or bus. You can even hire a bike to explore the city or surrounding countryside, with WunderLocke as your base.

The apartment in the very popular West-Schwabing district is in the immediate vicinity of the Olympiapark (3 min walk) and Luitpoldpark (2 min walk) and is well connected to public transport.

In the nearby Olympiapark there are events or sporting events, there is the SEA LIFE underwater world and you can either relax in the countryside /on a boat trip / in the beer garden (including swimming, fitness, ice sports, trampoline /open-air cinema, etc.)

Nearby is also the BMW Museum and the BMW Welt (5 min walk). And the biggest shopping center in the city - the OEZ - can be reached in 4 minutes by metro.

name: One Bedroom Open Plan Suite at Schwan Locke
description:
Welcome to your new mid-century-inspired base in the Bavarian capital, minutes from the site of Oktoberfest.

The vibe is one of calm creativity. The community is open and inclusive. And the apartments are both spacious and sophisticated. Settle in and see a side to Munich most tourists miss.
neighborhood_overview:
In Munich for Oktoberfest, Frühlingsfest or the Tollwood Winterfestival? You couldn’t stay in a better-located hotel or apartment. Just minutes from Theresienwiese, Schwan Locke offers an inspiring tranquil retreat in the midst of the action.

Our local borough, Isarvorstadt, includes the pretty neighbourhood of Glockenbackviertel, with its coffee shops, gay bars, global foodie spots and independent shops. And if your itinerary includes sightseeing time, we’re just a few tram stops from the city’s main attractions too. Including Marienplatz, the Viktualienmarkt, Beergarden Augustiner Keller and the museum quarter. Munich, done properly.

description: The approx. 25 m² apartment Copacabana with kitchenette offers everything you need, no matter how long you intend to stay. host_about: Many years ago, our founder, Amos, travelled to Rio, completely exhausted by daily life, and rediscovered himself there. The tolerance for people from all backgrounds, the palpable love for life, and the natural warmth of the Cariocas inspired Amos to make Brazil his second home. Rioca is a place where guests can experience what he did in Rio: The feeling of being home, surrounded by friends. Enter through our doors and experience the world of Brazilian warmth that turns strangers into friends. Whether for one night or many, whether alone or with others, everyone is welcome. Rioca is a place where life feels easy. In your apartment you can cook to your heart’s content in your very own kitchen and enjoy deep restful sleep

neighborhood_overview: Away from the hustle and bustle of the city, you'll be located in Au-Haidhausen- a friendly residential area. Au-Haidhausen offers something different from the rest of Munich; authenticity and a strong sense of community of which you'll become a part. Kultfabric and Optimolwerke are the most famous places around here, with Kultfabrik being one of the largest party zones in Europe (25 diverse nightclubs in this area). With plenty of transportation options, you can get anywhere anytime.

Or you can visit the traditional beer gardens such as Harlachingen garden city (about 1 km walk), Harlachinger Einkehr, Kugler Alm (drink "Radler" was invented here), Menterschwaige (next to Lola Montez and King Ludwig I), jazz beer garden "Wawi" (forestry in Grosshesselohe), etc.

Enjoy what you're up to!
host_about:
Bin in München geboren, wie auch meine Eltern und zum Teil meine Großeltern.
Auch mein Sohn ist in München geboren ist aber zur Hälfte US-Bürger. Englisch ist also kein Problem. Wir haben 3 Jahre in NY State gewohnt.
Zu meiner Studentenzeitung war ich auch mal 6 Monate in Paris. Aber mein Französisch ist etwas eingerostet, für kleine Anfragen und Auskünfte stehe ich gerne zur Verfügung und tue mein Bestes.
Wünsche einen angenehmen Aufenthalt in meiner schönen Heimatstadt und hoffe ich kann Euch jederzeit weiterhelfen wenn ihr was von hier wissen möchtet.
Viel Spaß oder ‚a guade Zeit mit vui Gaudi‘
Claudia

name: Brera "Cosy" Apartment - Your Long Stay Rate
description: The cozy studio apartment with fully equipped kitchenette is stylish and warm at the same time. It offers you a cozy home away from home with all the amenities like weekly cleaning, use of the laundromat and simple digital check-in, 24/7. The large desk will make it easier for you to work from the apartment. The local team is here to help you every step of the way.
host_about:
Buongiorno und herzlich Willkommen in München Schwabing. Wir freuen uns sehr darauf, dich hier begrüßen zu dürfen.

Schwabing war schon immer der lebendige Stadtteil München, in dem nicht nur viele Kunstschaffende ihr zu Hause hatten, sondern Studierende, Touristen, „Business People“ von jung bis alt in den lebendigen Restaurants und Bars nebeneinander saßen. Und noch heute ist genau dieses Bild hier zu finden. Wir wünschen dir eine schöne Zeit bei uns, helfen dir mit der Wahl des richtigen Restaurants, deinem Weg zur Arbeit oder verraten dir die schönste Joggingstrecke im Olympiapark – direkt hinter dem Haus.

Wir sind für dich da. Ciao!

Dein Brera München Schwabing Guest Relation Team

neighborhood_overview:
Maxvorstadt was meant to be a center for art, culture, and science right from the start. Significant is the high number of cultural and artistic institutions, significant museums and collections:

Old and New Pinakothek, Lenbachhaus with art construction, graphic collection, glyptothek and the State Antique Collections and the Museum of Church Art in Georgian belong to the Maxvorstadt.

With the Pinakothek der Moderne, Museum Brandhorst and the Egyptian State Collection, you will find more cultural and architectural highlights in the district.

host_about:
Buongiorno und herzlich Willkommen in München Schwabing. Wir freuen uns sehr darauf, dich hier begrüßen zu dürfen.

Schwabing war schon immer der lebendige Stadtteil München, in dem nicht nur viele Kunstschaffende ihr zu Hause hatten, sondern Studierende, Touristen, „Business People“ von jung bis alt in den lebendigen Restaurants und Bars nebeneinander saßen. Und noch heute ist genau dieses Bild hier zu finden. Wir wünschen dir eine schöne Zeit bei uns, helfen dir mit der Wahl des richtigen Restaurants, deinem Weg zur Arbeit oder verraten dir die schönste Joggingstrecke im Olympiapark – direkt hinter dem Haus.

Wir sind für dich da. Ciao!

Dein Brera München Schwabing Guest Relation Team

name: Sporty Fit: Maisonette with training mirror
description: Above the roofs of Munich in the district of Gern: our maisonettes with fully equipped kitchen and own living, dining and home office area including free high-speed wifi are located in the green and directly at the Olympic Park. In the living area there is also a modern training mirror, which offers fitness enthusiasts over 300 workouts from different areas.
neighborhood_overview: We are right in the middle of one of the most popular residential areas of the city: in Nymphenburg, Neuhausen and Gern free living space is hotly sought after, because here it is incredibly beautiful and very green: from the hotel you are in a few minutes walk directly in the Olympic area with its many sports, leisure and sightseeing opportunities such as Sea World, BMW Museum, the TV tower, the ice rink and the large weekend flea market. Just as quickly, you can walk to the Dante Stadium, which also has its winter outdoor swimming pool open during the cold season, or to the Taxispark and the associated Taxis beer garden: a real highlight, especially in the summer. For coffee and cake connoisseurs, we recommend the insider tip Café Tribeca at the end of the street. An extra plus point is the proximity to Nymphenburg Palace with its parks, the two driveways and the canal, the best place in town for curling or ice skating in winter.

name: Grand Apartment close to the Isar and Citycenter
description:
Enjoy freedom and flexibility. Homaris apartments offer you a home in a foreign city. Be independent, because we have already prepared everything for you.
Whether it's a city trip with friends or a business trip, alone or with your team - we offer accommodations in different sizes in different cities.
Our apartments impress with modern design, a central location and amenities that leave nothing to be desired. Each apartment at Homaris tells its own story - is individual. Just like you!
neighborhood_overview: The Glockenbachviertel is considered to be the center of Munich's trend scene. The famous bars and nightclubs are open until the early hours of the morning. One of the highlights is the State Theater at Gärtnerplatz. There are also boutiques, galleries and an art museums. The riverbank areas of the Isar are closed by. They are popular places for cycling, walking, recreation and barbecuing. Swimming and boating in the Isar is permitted in certain areas, as is surfing - always at your own risk. The near by "Flaucher" is probably Munich's best-known Isar beach and a popular meeting place.
host_about:
"I am originally from the south of Germany but have been living in Berlin for over five years. I have travelled all over the world and am open-minded and enjoy meeting people from all walks of life. 

I love travelling, football and documentaries!

I’ve been running my own business for several years now meaning that I’m working most of the day, but easily contactable by phone and ready to help out whenever needed."

Lived the corporate  life and now into spirituality and personal development.

name: Modernes Apartment im Grünen am Olympiapark
description: Super quiet and in the middle of the greenery, it lives in our new, stylish serviced apartments right at the Olympiapark. Whether short or longstay, business or leisure, everything is taken care of here: kitchenette, dining, work and living area, marble bathroom. There is an in-house laundry room, as well as free high-speed Wi-Fi. And: we are very central in Neuhausen, where Munich is colorful and lively and you can easily walk everywhere
neighborhood_overview: We are right in the middle of one of the most popular residential areas in the city: in Nymphenburg, Neuhausen and Gern, free living space is in high demand, because here it is incredibly beautiful and very green: from the hotel you are in a few minutes' walk directly in the Olympic grounds with its many sports, leisure and sightseeing options such as Sea World, BMW Museum, the TV Tower, the Eishalle and the large weekend flea market. Just as quickly, you are in the Dantestadium on foot, which is also open to the cold season of the winter warming pool or in the taxi park and the associated taxi beer garden: a real highlight, especially in the summer. For coffee and cake editors we recommend the secret tip cafe Tribeca at the end of the road. Clearly an extra plus point is the proximity to the Nymphenburg Castle all year round with its parks, the two driveways and the castle canal, the best place in town for curling or ice skating in winter

Wir sind Gastgeber:innen aus Leidenschaft und bieten Dir ein zweites Zuhause außerhalb der pulsierenden Großstadt im Grünen. Wir freuen uns Dich in unserem Living Hotel am Olympiapark willkommen zu heißen und zu Deinem Rückzugsort in München zu werden.

We are passionate hosts and offer you a second home outside of the vibrant city surrounded by nature. With the Olympic Park right on your doorstep, we do not only offer you a quiet atmosphere for work and everyday life, but also a perfect connection to the city center. We're looking forward to welcoming you and making our Living Hotel am Olympiapark your haven in Munich.

name: limehome Munich Fritz-Erler Str. | Suite
description: At limehome, we believe that everyone deserves a better place while traveling. A place to look forward to return to. A place designed to stay®. Whether you are looking for a home away from home or a quiet place to work - our apartments feature high-quality fittings including a premium hotel bed for restful nights & suite dreams. Our digital-enabled guest journey without a physical reception and staff on-site makes your stay more convenient.
neighborhood_overview: Our suites are located in the centre of Munich's Neuperlach district. In this lively neighbourhood in the south-east of the Bavarian capital, you are just a short walk away from everything you need. Along Fritz-Erler Straße and in the surrounding area, you will find a variety of shops, bars and restaurants. From local shops to cosy cafés, there is something for every taste. With the underground and bus connections, you can reach the rest of the city in just a few minutes and at the same time take a break from the hustle and bustle of Munich in the numerous green spaces in the neighbourhood. Not only will you find the usual limehome standard for your stay here, but also the ideal location to experience the beauty and diversity of Munich up close.

name: Schönes Zimmer - mitten im Zentrum/ Museumsviertel
description:
Beautiful, bright, large room in the middle of Munich city centre.
The room is equipped with a large desk, a spacious closet, a comfortable, freshly made bed and a cozy couch.

The apartment is absolutely centrally located in the museum and university district of Maxvorstadt in Munich. The subway stop Theresienstraße is 1 min. to walk. The Munich main train station is a 15-minute walk and can be reached in 5-10 minutes by subway, the Sendlinger Tor in 15 minutes.
host_about:
Hi there! :)
I’m Kerstin, 32 years old (sigh!). 
Speaking from a professional perspective, I’m a sworn translator and linguist, just finished an additional Masters in Legal Translation. 

Besides, trying to fight climate change from my home desk by writing for “Klimanews Podcast”, a German politically independent news podcast about climates change and sustainability.

Very much looking forward to welcome you guys in Munich! :-)

host_about:

neighborhood_overview: Here, in the Haidhausen district, many Munich people prefer to live, because here you get the best of two worlds: Munich pulsates here. It's colorful, creative and  cosmopolitan, but also green and completely relaxed. From the hotel, you can take public transport, which starts right outside the door, within minutes to the most beautiful and exciting corners of the city: Maximilianstraße, Marienplatz, Viktualienmarkt, Wiener Platz or the Museum Triangle in Schwabing. But here you are already in the middle of city life and can easily walk to the neighborhood from the Gasteig cultural center to the Isar, the Müllersche Volksbad, the Deutsche Museum, the Stadtcafe Film Museum, the shopping street Motorama and also the oldest cinema in the city "Die Museum Lichtspiele" on foot.

It's colorful, creative and  cosmopolitan, but also green and completely relaxed. From the hotel, you can take public transport, which starts right outside the door, within minutes to the most beautiful and exciting corners of the city: Maximilianstraße, Marienplatz, Viktualienmarkt, Wiener Platz or the Museum Triangle in Schwabing. But here you are already in the middle of city life and can easily walk to the neighborhood from the Gasteig cultural center to the Isar, the Müllersche Volksbad, the Deutsche Museum, the Stadtcafe Film Museum, the shopping street Motorama and also the oldest cinema in the city "Die Museum Lichtspiele" on foot.
host_about:
Wir sind Gastgeber:innen aus Leidenschaft. Im schönen Haidhausen direkt am Deutschen Museum, im Zentrum Münchens bieten wir Dir familiäre Gastfreundschaft. Mit zahlreichen Einkaufsmöglichkeiten, Cafés und Restaurants in der nächsten Umgebung sind wir Deine Anlaufstelle rechts der Isar.

We are passionate hosts. In beautiful Haidhausen, directly at the Deutsches Museum, in the heart of Munich, we offer you cosy hospitality. With numerous shops, cafés and restaurants in the immediate vicinity, we are your contact point on the Isar river bank.

Munich is a vibrant city known for its rich history, stunning architecture, and cultural heritage. Nestled along the banks of the River Isar, Munich blends old-world charm with modern urban energy. Its landmarks, like the iconic Marienplatz, Nymphenburg Palace, and the Frauenkirche, reflect its medieval and royal past. The city is a hub for art and culture, housing world-class museums like the Alte Pinakothek and the Deutsches Museum, and it celebrates Bavarian traditions, most famously through Oktoberfest. Munich also offers a thriving economy, a well-established beer culture with traditional beer gardens, and proximity to the picturesque Bavarian Alps, making it a beloved destination for both locals and tourists.

Here are a few things to do while your here:
✔ Oktoberfest - Only a short 3 minute walk from the apartment, visit Munich’s iconic annual beer festival
✔ Explore Marienplatz: Visit the iconic square and watch the Neues Rathaus glockenspiel.
✔ Tour Ny
